eased on parole in 2003 (roughly 11,000 individuals) for the next seven years, providing a comprehensive view of their postprison neighborhoods, families, employment, and contact with the parole system. On the Outside delivers a powerful combination of hard data and personal narrative that shows why our country continues to struggle with the social and economic reintegration of the formerly incarcerated. For further information, please visit ontheoutsidebook.us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEmployment re-entryzUnited States. 0aPrisonersxDeinstitutionalizationzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  acriminal justice.  aemployment.  amass incarceration.  aparole.  apoverty.  aprisoner reentry.  arace.  arehabilitation.  areintegration.  astigma.1 aMorenoff, Jeffrey D., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWyse, Jessica J. B., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226607788423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226607788/original  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press C